      "text": "An ateleological design process - as opposed to a [[Teleological Design]] process - does not aim to achieve some objectively developed goal. Instead its aim, as suggested by Introna (1996) [https://sites.google.com/site/lucasintrona/home/journal-publications/publication-archive-1-1/NotesonAteleologicaldevelopment.pdf PDF paper] is to maintain the wholeness and harmony of whatever systems/context in which it takes place."
